          "title": "The final summons — last words of the public ministry",
          "body": "12:44-50 functions as John’s apostolic summary of Jesus’ entire public message — not a new event but the chapter’s coda. Jesus *cried out* (the verb *krazo* signals public proclamation) and named the heart of everything He has said: faith in Him is faith in the Father (12:44); seeing Him is seeing the Father (12:45); He came as Light into the world (12:46); His mission is salvation, not condemnation (12:47); yet the word He spoke will judge at the last day (12:48); and every word He spoke was the Father’s commandment, which is eternal life (12:50). The public ministry of Jesus ends with a summons that gathers up every theme of John 1–11. From 13:1 onward, Jesus speaks only to His own."
